                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d177">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/43</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-02T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5522. Your 7251, September 25, 4 p.m. You may confirm to British Government
                    impression conveyed by your note that this Government feel they can not properly
                    prevent the rye from reaching Sweden. The arrangement for taking over the wheat
                    for the Belgian Relief was approved by <persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PLE1">Lord Eustace Percy</persName>, and
                    subsequent change of position was most embarrassing. It is hoped the British
                    Government will see their way to granting permit for export of rye to Sweden
                    without delay. Please report by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
